        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 6 at 3:56PM MDT until September 6 at 4:30PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>SVRSLC

The National Weather Service in Salt Lake City has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Kane County in southern Utah...

* Until 430 PM MDT.

* At 354 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 21 miles southwest
of Glen Canyon National Recreation Area, or 36 miles southeast of
Escalante, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.

* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
northeastern Kane County, including near Coyote Gulch on Hole-in-
the-Rock Road.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Large hail and continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring
with this storm. Move indoors immediately.
Lightning is one of nature's leading killers. Remember, if you can
hear thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
